# No fix available upstream for these CVEs as of 2026-05-04.
# Each entry should have a corresponding rationale paragraph in
# docs/trivy-rationale.md. The Trivy CI gate runs with
# `ignore-unfixed: true`, so these unfixed-upstream CVEs are
# already filtered out today; this list exists so the day someone
# flips `ignore-unfixed: false` we don't get a wall of failures
# for issues that have no remediation.

# ncurses: buffer overflow (affected, no fix released)
CVE-2025-69720

# systemd: arbitrary code execution via spurious IPC (affected, no fix released)
CVE-2026-29111

# openssh-client: required for Ansible; no fix released
CVE-2026-35385
CVE-2026-35386
CVE-2026-35414

# libexpat1: integer-overflow info disclosure (affected, no fix released as of 2026-04-24)
CVE-2026-25210

# libnghttp2-14: post-session-termination DoS (affected, no fix released as of 2026-04-24)
CVE-2026-27135

# libcap2: capability handling flaw, no fix released as of 2026-05-04
CVE-2026-4878

# libgnutls30t64: TLS-side issue, no fix released as of 2026-05-04
CVE-2026-33845
